OL,3,CReform UK deputy leader at Birmingham
OL,4,Celection count as Labour losses
OL,5,Cexpected
OL,7,FReform UK's deputy leader Richard Tice
OL,8,Fhas arrived at the Birmingham City
OL,9,FCouncil election count to celebrate
OL,10,Fhis party's gains there.
OL,12,FFinal results aren't expected until
OL,13,Fafter 6pm but Tice has said the party
OL,14,F"absolutely smashed it" in other areas
OL,15,Fof the West Midlands, including
OL,16,FNewcastle-under-Lyme and Tamworth.
OL,18,FNewcastle-under-Lyme was the party's
OL,19,Ffirst council win of these local
OL,20,Felections, and in Tamworth the council
OL,21,Fwent to no overall control.
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@WO]
