OL,3,CReform UK deputy leader at Birmingham
OL,4,Celection count as Labour losses
OL,5,Cexpected
OL,7,FHe added that the results already in
OL,8,Fin the region amounted to voters
OL,9,Fsaying "yes, we are going to give you
OL,10,Fan extra chance to do even better".
OL,12,FA Labour source in Birmingham has told
OL,13,Four political reporter Lewis Warner,
OL,14,F"We always knew the elections in
OL,15,FBirmingham would be tough, and the
OL,16,Fcombination of local issues and the
OL,17,Fwider national picture is making for a
OL,18,Fvery difficult set of results."
OL,26,@qD@HOUrD@bO]vD@AOU
